### 1. Get Initial Feed (Page 1)
GET http://localhost:8999/api/v1/feed?userId=user123&limit=10
Accept: application/json

### 2. Get Next Page (using cursor from previous response)
# Note: You'll need to manually replace the cursor here with the one from the first response.
# For testing logic, we'll use a known timestamp from our seed (e.g., now - 1000)
GET http://localhost:8999/api/v1/feed?userId=user123&limit=10&cursor=1714278000
Accept: application/json

### 3. Track Views
POST http://localhost:8999/api/v1/feed/views
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user123",
  "articleIds": ["art_0", "art_1", "art_2"]
}

### 4. Get Feed Again (art_0, art_1, art_2 should be filtered out)
GET http://localhost:8999/api/v1/feed?userId=user123&limit=10
Accept: application/json
